<span id="freeTextContainer1270385884002818640">Wow! I don&apos;t really know what to say about this book. The prose was a bit &quot;fancy&quot; for me but the story, I think, is very important. Being that the author was there, I&apos;m assuming it is an accurate portrayal of the horrors of the war. It is such a sad and horrible story but also a very good story (does that make sense?). It is hard to imagine what these young men and women go through and then to come back here and try to live a &quot;normal&quot; life, seems almost impossible. This has been made into a movi</span>
  <span id="freeText1270385884002818640" style="display:none">Wow! I don't really know what to say about this book. The prose was a bit "fancy" for me but the story, I think, is very important. Being that the author was there, I'm assuming it is an accurate portrayal of the horrors of the war. It is such a sad and horrible story but also a very good story (does that make sense?). It is hard to imagine what these young men and women go through and then to come back here and try to live a "normal" life, seems almost impossible. This has been made into a movie. It will be heart wrenching to watch. </span>
